        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 8:32PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 832 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Yuma, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Yuma around 835 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
northeastern Colorado.</instruction>
